The police's Noloyiso Rwexana says the suspect was apprehended following a tip-off from the public. CAPE TOWN A Belhar resident has been arrested for being in the possession of West Coast lobsters worth an estimated R50,000.Police arrested the 32-year-old man on the N2 highway near Sir Lowry's Pass earlier today.Officers found numerous bags containing whole lobsters and lobster tails in his vehicle.The police's Noloyiso Rwexana says the suspect was apprehended following a tip-off from the public.&quot;They recovered numerous containers with lobsters and lobster tails. The driver was arrested and he will appear in court tomorrow.&quot;(Edited by Shimoney Regter)